**Abstract:**
Essay dated September 2, 1993, titled "Draft 3: The Professionalization of Theology." The document engages with Frei's "Types of Christian Theology" to analyze the shift from pre-revolutionary patristic commentary to post-revolutionary scholastic Summae. It develops an extensive analysis of biblical commentary as subordination to the text vs. argumentative demonstration. Central argument: understanding linguistic meaning is not being informed of intention but fulfilling communicative intention practically. The "meaning fallacy" arises from treating the pure contemplator's case as paradigmatic.

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay on theology's professionalization; develops philosophy of language relevant to biblical hermeneutics.

